1968 _ The Lucy Show is redesigned and becomes Here's Lucy. Earlier in the year, they have their first child. 1967 _ Miss Ball sells company to Gulf &amp; Western for $18 million.  1957 _ Desilu purchases RKO studios and begins producing other programs. 1926 _ Begins career in show business in New York as a chorus girl. It runs until 1974. 1961 _ Miss Ball marries night-club comic Gary Morton, who becomes her executive producer. Here are highlights of Lucille Ball's career: 1911 _ Born Aug 6, 1911, in Jamestown NY, the daughter of an electrician and concert pianist Desiree Ball. 